<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southeast China City Holds Telephone Card Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Telephone card collectors from Hong
Kong, Taiwan and China's inland area were in Fuzhou, southeast
China's Fujian Province, to attend a telephone card show today, to
greet Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by local telecom authorities and phone card fans,
the exhibition is the largest of its kind ever held in the
province.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 telephone cards from 30 countries and regions
were on display, and seminars about the use of the card were held.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou introduced telephone cards in 1989. They have found
growing favor among the country's collectors and are second only
to stamp collecting as a popular hobby.  
</P>
</TEXT>
