<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia, Malaysia to Bring Islands Dispute to Int'l </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia and Malaysia have finally
signed an agreement to bring the two countries' dispute over
Sipadan and Ligitan islands to the International Court of Justice
(ICJ) in the Hague.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Foreign Ministry in a press statement here said
Foreign Minister Ali Alatas and his Malaysian counterpart Dato
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi signed the agreement in Kuala Lumpur today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached during the informal ASEAN foreign
ministers' meeting there, said the press statement.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN (the Association of Southeast Asian Nations) groups
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand
and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
In the agreement, Indonesia and Malaysia would put to the ICJ's
hand to decide the ownership status of the islands based on the
agreed legal procedures.
</P>
<P>
"We all realize that territorial disputes of any kind can
occasion tension that may exacerbate the bilateral relations
between the disputants, particularly if they fail to arrive at an
understanding on how to resolve it amicably," Alatas was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
"An amicable solution could be reached through a political
settlement or through the involvement of a third neutral party in
an adjudication process," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the settlement of the dispute would in turn contribute
to efforts to maintain peace and security in the Southeast Asian
region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Abdullah Badawi said the agreement indicates the two
countries' readiness to accept an ICJ decision as "final and
binding."
</P>
<P>
The dispute over Ligitan and Sipadan islands, off the coast of
Malaysia's Sabah state and Indonesia's East Kalimantan province,
has been a thorn in the relations between the two neighbors since
1969 when both laid a claim to them.
</P>
<P>
In October last year, the two countries agreed to refer the
dispute to the ICJ after failing to reach a settlement through
bilateral negotiations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
