<HEADLINE> Rasmussen Enters Final at Badminton Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Denmark's Peter Rasmussen
beat Indonesia's Heryanto Arbi to enter men's singles final at the
world badminton championships here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The student doctor, who never beat Arbi in their past four
encounters since 1995, rallied from one set down to gain a 9-15,
15-9, 15-2 victory in a 76-minute-long semi-final.
</P>
<P>
"Actually I didn't expect to win. His attacks are very good. I
just played relaxed. If you are too tense, you cannot play your
normal game," said Rasmussen after the match.
</P>
<P>
"I just take it easy and enjoy playing badminton," he added.
</P>
<P>
He will meet China's Sun Jun or compatriot Poul-Erik
Hoyer-Larsen in Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
On his chance against either of two, Rasmussen said, "Both are
dangerous."
</P>
<P>
Sun is due to meet Hoyer-Larsen in another semi-final later
Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
