<HEADLINE> France Sends Warship to Sierra Leone to Evacuate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- France has sent a warship to the
capital of Sierra Leone to evacuate foreigners, reported the
Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
The French warship is now mooring at a quay not far from the
Mamie Yoko Hotel, where about 1,000 foreigners, many of them
Lebanese merchants, were waiting to leave the city.
</P>
<P>
The United States helicopter-carrier USS Kearsarge has
evacuated 900 foreigners from Freetown in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
Germany, the United States, France and Britain have called on
their nationals to leave Sierra Leone, where a coup d'etat took
place on May 25.
</P>
<P>
Lootings have occurred in Freetown, and a West African force is
likely to intervene to restore the country's deposed civilian
president, Ahmed Tejan Kabbah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
