<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Currency Devalues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian currency Birr
continued devaluation at the 130th weekly foreign exchange
auction held today.
</P>
<P>
The National Bank of Ethiopia said in a statement that the
official exchange rate will be 6.702 Birr for one U.S. Dollar
from June 2 to 8, compared with 6.673 Birr for one Dollar in the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
The bank said the highest bid rate was 6.932 Birr whereas the
lowest bid rate was 6.615 Birr for one Dollar, adding that the
volume of foreign exchange make available at the auction amounted
to 15 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia introduced the foreign exchange auction system in
1993. 
</P>
