<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ma's Runners Show Poor Results in China Athletics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, China, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Ma Junren, who coached "Ma
Family Army" to win three gold medals in the 1993 Athletics
Worlds, tossed his head in dismay about the poor results showed by
his women runners at the Chinese national track and field
championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Don't expect my runners and me to create the miracle again
before the next century," shouted Ma, who guided Wang Junxia, Qu
Yunxia and Liu Dong to beat the world in the Stuttgart World
Championships and set three world records in the 1,500, 3,000,
10,000 meters in 1993.
</P>
<P>
With Olympic 5,000-meter champion Wang Junxia pulling out this
meet due to poor health condition, world 1,500-meter record holder
Qu struggled hard in her thrump event, finishing 10th in 4 minutes
48.25 seconds, almost one minute slower than her personal best.
</P>
<P>
"I'm finished. Injuries and illness have bothered me a lot
these years. It will be my last year on the track, next season
I'll be an assistant coach," said the 27-year-old Qu.
</P>
<P>
Wang Junxia and Liu Dong broke away from Ma's camp in 1994
after a bitter dispute with the coach. The two talented girls now
are coached by Mao Dezhen.
</P>
<P>
But Liu, who won the 800-meter gold in Stuttgart, only managed
6th in the 1,500 meters in 4:29.34. The top three places were won
by Yan Wei in 4:13.49, Liu Liping in 4:18.98 and Wang Qingfen in
4:19.07.
</P>
<P>
With Qu and Liu already lost their competitive abilities, Wang
remains the only hope for China's athletics. But after the Olympic
triumph in Atlanta, Wang is losing her interest in running.
</P>
<P>
"She has stopped training since last October. She said she had
been bothered by a consistant headache. Many people persuaded her
to stick on, but she said she just wants to quit. I can do nothing
about it, even though I am her coach," said Mao.
</P>
<P>
"I guess she wants to rest for a while. Wang will not compete
in the World Championships this August," Mao added.
</P>
<P>
It was said that Wang and Coach Ma are still like water and
fire, hating each other. One of the reasons is Ma refused to give
Wang the Mercedes Benz car which Wang won as a gift at the
Stuttgart Worlds. "No way, it is not belong to you," Ma was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Ma is coaching a new army including many teenage runners. Ma
said, "Now I've laid my sights on the 2,000 Sydney Olympics. I'm
sure there young girls will be good enough by then." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
