<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Rebuilding Treaty of Nanking Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Repair of an exhibition hall in a
temple where the Treaty of Nanking negotiations took place in the
capital of East China's Jiangsu Province has been completed here
today.
</P>
<P>
The treaty was signed on a British naval ship in August 1842,
ceding Hong Kong to Britain, and forcing China to pay an indemnity
of 21,000,000 silver dollars, along with other humiliating
things. The treaty marked the start of colonization of China by
western imperialist powers.
</P>
<P>
The original exhibition hall, which contains historical
documents on the Treaty of Nanking, was built in 1990. Jiangsu and
other local governments spent over five million yuan last year on
renovating the temple, which was built in 1425.
</P>
<P>
The hall's size was tripled to 2,100 sq. m. It also contains
more than 1,100 treaties China signed with western powers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970601.0043 </DOCNO>
