<HEADLINE> First Municipal CPC Committee For Fourth Chinese Municipality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party Committee of
Chongqing, which was made a municipality directly under the the
central government in March this year, has been elected.
</P>
<P>
At the final session of the city's first CPC congress today,
the Municipal Party Committee and the Municipal Party Commission
for Discipline Inspection were elected.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Delin was elected secretary of the Municipal CPC
Committee, and Pu Haiqing, Wang Yunlong, Liu Zhizhong and Wang
Hongju were chosen as deputy secretaries.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, who is 58, was born in Beijing, and graduated from
Beijing's Qinghua University in 1964. He taught at Gansu
Polytechnic University. He also held positions of president of
Gansu Polytechnic University, secreatary of the Party Committee of
the Harbin Boiler Plant, Mayor of Harbin, and vice-minister of the
Machine-Building Industry.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing used to be under Sichuan government control but now
is the country's fourth municipality following Beijing, Shanghai
and Tianjin. 
</P>
