<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East Chinese City Builds "Warning Bell" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held this morning
for the new "Warning Bell" in Jinhai Temple in Nanjing, the
capital of east China's Jiangsu province.
</P>
<P>
This bell will mark the first unequal treaty of modern Chinese
history, referred to as the "Nanjing Treaty", which was signed 155
years ago, in which the government of the Qing Dynasty ceded Hong
Kong to the British government.
</P>
<P>
Since March, students and other people in Nanjing have made
donations for casting the bell which is meant to remind the
Chinese people of the humiliation China suffered, but also to
welcome Hong Kong's return to the motherland,
</P>
<P>
The 3.5-ton, 1.84-meter-high bronze bell has a seal cut at its
top from an inscription by Chen Huanyou, secretary of the Jiangsu
Provincial Committee of the Chinese Communist Party. It describes
the glorious struggle the Chinese people have waged against
foreign invaders since 1840.
</P>
<P>
The bell was rung today by provincial government and Nanjing
military region leaders and student representatives for the
ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
