<HEADLINE> Iran, Iraq Swap Remains of Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Iraq today exchanged
remains of their soldiers who were killed during the eight year
war between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to Iran's official news agency IRNA, the remains of
67 Iraqi soldiers and 20 Iranian combatants were swapped at the
border crossing of Khosravi.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier General Mir Faisal Baqerzadeh, head of Iran's
committee in charge of searching for those missing in action,
said that these Iranian soldiers lost their lives in Sumar and
Mandali fronts, some 150 kilometers east of Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Iraq agreed on Sunday to launch a joint search
operation to locate bodies left from the 1980-88 war, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The committee affiliated to the Armed Forces Command
Headquarters has so far discovered the remains of 33,000 Iranian
soldiers and returned them to their families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
