<HEADLINE> Indonesia Ties Uzbekistan in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia drew Uzbekistan 1-1 in
their World Cup soccer Asian zone Group eight qualifier here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
As both sides failed in their five corner kicks apiece,
Indonesian captain Sudirman converted from the spot in the 35th
minute as Uzbekistan goalkeeper was caught of grasping the leg of
an Indonesian forward.
</P>
<P>
After the break, the visitors staged tough attacks with five
attempts against the Indonesian goal, and the equaliser was scored
in the 72nd minute by Oleg Shatskikh who ran from the midfield
before slamming home for Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
Following are the group standings with games played, won,
drawn, lost, goals for, against and points:
</P>
<P>
Uzbekistan 3  2  1  0  8  1  7
</P>
<P>
