<HEADLINE> Russia Wins Handball World Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Russia defeated Sweden 23-21 in a
tight match to take its second men's Handball World Championship
in Kumamoto, Japan on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Russia, the 1993 world champion, led 11-10 at halftime as
goalie Andrei Lavrov made 12 saves, and Valeri Gopine scored five
goals for the winners.
</P>
