<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Calls for Political Federation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
called today for developing the current East Africa Cooperation
(EAC) into a political federation in the region.
</P>
<P>
"My hope for the longer term is that our present cooperation
will develop into a political federation for east Africa, once
economic integration is in place," Moi noted.
</P>
<P>
The EAC, comprising Kenya, Tanzania and Uganda, is also
committed to the establishment of "a single market for east
Africa," he said here today when presiding over the celebrations
marking the Madaraka Day.
</P>
<P>
On the day 34 years ago, Kenya formed its self-government
and attained the right to manage its own affairs from British
colonialists.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian President Mkapa, together with tens of thousands of
Kenyans, attended the celebrations including a military review,
flying-past by Kenya's Air Forces, scouts' march, colorful dances
and choirs.
</P>
<P>
The peaceful celebrations came just one day after the police
broke up a banned rally organized by the opposition for
constitutional reforms at the Uhuru Park of Nairobi yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Fierce running battles between the police and opposition
sympathizers lasted several hours Saturday, leaving at least
dozens of people injured and a complete standstill of businesses
in the city. Some cars and shopwindows were smashed.
</P>
<P>
In response, Moi reiterated today that no change in the
Constitution will be made before the forthcoming general
elections.
</P>
<P>
"The Constitution that has served us so well should therefore
not be subjected to changes that are designed to satisfy
short-term interests," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Even discussions on the Constitution can only be held
meaningfully after the general elections and then a commission
concerned will be appointed, said Moi.
</P>
<P>
He added that a new law -- the Peaceful Assemblies Bill --
will soon replace the current Public Order Act. However, he did
not reveal the main points of the new bill. enditem


