<HEADLINE> East Chinese City Puts Up Statue of Communist Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A statue of Hu Qiaomu, a
theoretician of the Communist Party of China, was unveiled in
Yancheng City in east China's Jiangsu Province today to mark the
85th anniversary of his birth.
</P>
<P>
A number of people, including Hu Sheng, vice-chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, and Hu's family members, attended the unveiling
ceremony today.
</P>
<P>
The white marble statue -- 2.2 meters high and 1.5 meters wide
