<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A passenger bus rammed a shed and a
house, and then fell into a ravine in the northern Philippines
this morning, killing a bakery owner and seriously injuring 21
passengers.
</P>
<P>
According to a Philippine News Agency report, the accident
occurred when the bus, which was on its way from Cubao to Matnog,
Camarines Norte Province, tried to evade an oncoming truck. It
instead crashed onto a shed and a house.
</P>
<P>
The 75-year-old bakery owner, identified as So Kong, died of
head injuries on the spot, the report said. The injured were
rushed to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
The bus driver, who was also injured, surrendered himself to
the police, the report said.  
