<HEADLINE> Prices Drop in Vietnam in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's market prices dropped by 0.5
percent in May, the General Department of Statistics said.
</P>
<P>
Gold prices went down by 0.8 percent. Foodstuff prices across the
country dropped 0.6 percent and prices for garments, medicines
and fuel decreased between 0.1 and 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The drop was attributed to a 3.4 percent fall in grain prices,
of which rice price decreased by 3.3 percent here and 3.1 percent
in Ho Chi Minh city. 
</P>
