<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Beats Australia in Hockey Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- World Cup champions Pakistan
defeated Australia to win their six-match field hockey
international series on goal aggregate in Melbourne on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistanis, showing admirable resolve, fought back from 1-0
down at halftime and the loss of Danish Kaleem, dismissed for
misconduct five minutes before the changeover, to beat Australia
3-1 in the sixth and final match of the series.
</P>
<P>
That left the series tied at three matches all, but Pakistan
claimed the series on goals scored throughout the six matches,
12-11.
</P>
<P>
In effect, Rahim Khan's 63rd minute score in Sunday's game gave
Pakistan the series.
</P>
<P>
Matthew Smith gave Australia the lead in the 32nd minute, but
Pakistan roared home, scoring three times in the second half --
Muhammad Khalid Jnr in the 38th minute, Kamran Ashraf in the 43rd
minute and Rahim Khan seven minutes from full-time.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan won the opening match of the series 3-2 in Perth on
May 21 before Australia won back-to-back games 3-2 and 2-1 in
Adelaide last weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistanis levelled the series with a 3-2 victory in Sydney
last Wednesday, before Australia pulled ahead after another close
tussle 3-2 in Canberra Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will be returning to Adelaide in October for the
six-nation Champions Trophy Tournament, which also features
Atlanta Olympic champions the Netherlands, as well as Spain,
Germany, South Korea and Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
