<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Envoy Stresses Need to Achieve Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 1 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) peace
envoy Miguel Moratinos has stressed the need to establish an
independent Palestinian economy to avoid the eruption of
violence, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos made the remarks at an assembly of Arab, Druse and
Beduin local authority heads who met Saturday near Tiberias to
protest the freeze in the peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos noted that it was the EU's financial assistance that
had helped the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) survive in
the past years.
</P>
<P>
Due to the frequent closure on the territories by Israel for
security reasons, the fledgling Palestinian economy, which is
largely dependent on Israel, suffers tremendously as workers are
often prevented from entering Israel to work, and goods and
merchants from flowing freely.
</P>
<P>
Warning that the EU aid would not last forever, Moratinos
stressed the importance of establishing Palestinian economic
independence in order to prevent widespread violence.
</P>
<P>
"But these efforts of European Union will have an end. We
need the Palestinian National Authority to have the autonomy to
export, to import and to freely establish a real economy
intergrated between Jordan and Israel," he said.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos' remarks came following recent reports about the
PNA's irregularities in using the financial aid from foreign
donor countries.
</P>
<P>
Late last month, an audit report compiled by the PNA Auditing
Office revealed that 323 million U.S. dollars -- almost 40
percent of the PNA budget -- had been misused and wasted by
ministries or corrupt officials. The 1997 PNA budget is set at
866 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian Council discussed the misuse of funds the
week before, accusing some officials of living far beyond their
salaries. PNA President Yasser Arafat has ordered investigation
into the financial irregularities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
