<HEADLINE> Nateq-Nouri Re-Elected Iranian Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Despite failure in recent
presidential election, Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri was re-elected
the speaker of the 270-seat Parliament for another one-year term
with a majority of votes.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that out of 243
deputies present in the open session of the Parliament this
morning, Nateq-Nouri secured 211 votes.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Nateq-Nouri was the only candidate for
the post. In the elections for the presiding board of the
Parliament last year, Nateq-Nouri had got 146 votes.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the re-election of Nateq-Nouri as
the parliament speaker indicates that the conservatives still
dominated the parliament and the dominance will pose a severe
challenge to open-minded President-elect Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
However, the report gave no explanation why Nateq-Nouri is
the only candidate in today's voting.
</P>
<P>
Today's English daily Iran News reported that the alliance of
left wing called the Society of Combatant Clergymen (SCC) and
pro-Rafsanjani faction called G-6 were to nominate former
interior minister Abdullah Nouri for speaker.
</P>
<P>
The conservative camp called the Association of Combatant
Clergymen (ACC) fielded Nateq-Nouri for the post of speaker.
</P>
<P>
The 54-year-old speaker, one of the main contenders in the
May 23 presidential elections, was defeated by his arch
contender Mohammad Khatami because he obtained only 24.9 percent
of the total votes cast in the election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
