<HEADLINE> Six Cattle Thieves Beaten to Death in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Six alleged cattle lifters were
beaten to death reportedly by villagers in the early hours of
Saturday in Demra County, dozens of kilometers southeast of the
Bangladeshi capital, Dhaka, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to police, a group of cattle lifters on board an
engine boat surrounded Dasherkandi Village to lift cattle while
the village petrol chased and managed to catch them.
</P>
<P>
Later, angry villagers attacked the cattle lifters and beat
them mercilessly, police said. As a result, six cattle lifters
aged around 30 died on the spot. The villagers finally left the
place after dumping their bodies into nearby wetland.
</P>
<P>
Receiving a tip on Saturday morning, a police squad from the
Demra Police Station rushed to the place of the incident and
recovered the bodies.
</P>
<P>
No arrest has been made so far, police sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
