<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Calls for Intensive Education of Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official today
called for enhanced education of China's young generation, who are
"the future of the motherland and hope of the nation."
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made
the call when meeting representatives of children and teachers here
on the International Children's Day.
</P>
<P>
Hu, who is also member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, extended congratulations to children and youngsters,
and those engaged in children's work across the country, on behalf
of the CPC Central Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that those who have been conferred the
title of "China's Good Youngster or Child" will become qualified
builders of and successors to the socialist cause with "lofty
ideals, moral integrity, a good education and a strong sense of
discipline".
</P>
<P>
"Under the strong leadership of the CPC Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core," Hu pointed out,"the whole Party and the
whole nation are holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, to greet
the return of Hong Kong and the convocation of the 15th CPC
National Congress with actual deeds, and to propel the reform and
opening up, and modernization drive into the new century."
</P>
<P>
He called on the whole party and the whole society to recognize
the importance of work on the young "from a strategic point of
view", by enhancing their education, especially by nurturing their
moral integrity and ideological awareness, as well as the overall
quality.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the legal rights and interests of the children
must be protected, acts that endanger their physical and mental
health be cracked down on, and a good social environment for their
healthy growth be created. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
