<HEADLINE> North China, ROk to Sponsor Student Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of middle school
students from north China's Hebei Province and the Republic of
Korea (ROK) will participate in camping activities in China and
Korea during their summer and winter vocations.
</P>
<P>
The activities will be sponsored by the Hebei International
Economic and Cultural Exchanges Center and a Korean company.
</P>
<P>
In August, Hebei and the ROK will each send 300 middle school
students to Beijing, from where they will visit the Bashang
Grasslands and Chengde City in Hebei Province, and listen to
lectures on history and have campfire parties and sports
activities.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent agreement, a number of Chinese students
will be sent to Korea for cultural exchanges this winter, and
China-ROK cultural exchanges will become an annual event in the
coming years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
