<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Dips Marginally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- India's annual rate of inflation
fell by 0.4 percentage points to 6 percent for the week ending May
17 from 6.04 percent for the previous week, the Press Trust of
India said today.
</P>
<P>
The rate of inflation during the corresponding week of 1996 was
4.42 percent.
</P>
<P>
The wholesale price index for "all commodities" (base
1981-82=100) moved up by 0.2 percent during the week under review
to 323.3 as against 322.8 the week before.
</P>
<P>
During the week under review, prices of commodities such as
poultry, chicken and fodder eased substantially.  
</P>
</TEXT>
