<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches Safe Drinking Water Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan National Water
Supply and Drainage Board (NWSDB) has recently launched a water
supply project with the aim of providing safe drinking water to
rural areas by the year 2010, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The NWSDB has started drilling 7,500 tube wells and will help
dig 1,000 deep wells per year in the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
This program is being implemented with the participation of the
rural community and its main objective is to make the rural people
aware of their responsibilities in maintaining the wells, the
report noted.
</P>
<P>
This rural water supply scheme was inaugurated by the NWSDB in
response to a decision taken by the U.N. International Drinking
water Supply Program.
</P>
<P>
The rural-level leadership and local skilled persons will play
a leading role in the project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
