<HEADLINE> Fire Destroys Hundreds of Houses in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A fire destroyed 127 shanty houses
in Palmerah, in the western part of Jakarta, capital of Indonesia,
Saturday, police here said today.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 people were left homeless in the fire, which
broke out in the mid-section of the area in the morning, when most
of the occupants were out to work. It was put out one and half
hours later and no fatalities were reported.
</P>
<P>
As the relatively small houses stood very close to one another,
the raging flames easily jumped from one house to another before a
dozen of fire engines arrived at the scene, police said.
</P>
<P>
An investigation of the mishap is under way, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
