<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Banker Calls for Flexibility in Labor Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Bank of Italy Governor Antonio Fazio
today appealed for flexibility in labor policy, saying that
Italy's high jobless rate and widespread irregularly employed
"black labor" are products of inflexible labor practices.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate in Italy is as high as 12.1 percent and
an estimated 2.4 million workers are irregularly employed.
</P>
<P>
The way of bringing black labor to surface is to find
incentives for flexibility in the use of labor and the wage by
deregulating rigid labor contracts, Fazio said.
</P>
<P>
Black labor is estimated to account for 8 percent of the total
work force. Irregular immigrant labor from outside the European
Union is about 2.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The central banker said an increase in investment is also
needed to get job creation moving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
