<HEADLINE> Indonesian Ruling Party Consolidates Poll Triumph </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's ruling Golkar party
continues to consolidate its election triumph by gathering more
votes in Saturday's counting.
</P>
<P>
The provisional vote counting results at 21:00 local time
Saturday showed that the Golkar collected 81,927,897 votes, out of
a total of 110,267,224.
</P>
<P>
The United Development Party (PPP) followed with 24,975,766
while the Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) lagged far behind with
only 3,363,561 votes.
</P>
<P>
The Golkar's votes represent 74 percent of the total, the PPP
23 percent and the PDI 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Based on the figures, the Golkar has won 312 seats in the House
of Representatives while the PPP 78 and the PDI only six.
</P>
<P>
Some 39 seats are still to be competed.
</P>
<P>
The PPP, Golkar and PDI are vying for 425 seats in the
500-member House of Representatives. The remaining 75 seats are
reserved for the Armed Forces whose members do not vote.
</P>
<P>
A total of 124,740,987 people were eligible to vote in the May
29 general election.
</P>
<P>
The Golkar won 68 percent of the vote in the 1992 election and
had been aiming for a 70.02-percent win this year. The PPP won 17
percent of the vote in 1992 and the PDI 15 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
