The dam, which was inaugurated on Saturday, will irrigate
44,550 hectares of land, enabling local farmers to grow more crops
than ever before, the official paper The New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
A hydropower project of the dam, which is scheduled to be
completed by September, will generate 12 megawatts of electricity.
</P>
<P>
The earth dam is 43.5 meters high and 765 meters long, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 78 dams have been completed in the country since
1988, irrigating more than 486,000 hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's gross domestic product registered a 5.8-percent
increase in 1996-97, in which agricultural production went up by
3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's rice export was recorded at 271,900 tons in 1996,
 compared with 637,100 tons in the previous year, according to
official figures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
