<HEADLINE> Fujian, Hong Kong Anticipate Close Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Coastal Fujian Province expects
closer co-operation with Hong Kong after China resumes the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
According to Provincial Governor He Guoqiang, Hong Kong has
been Fujian's largest trade partner, accounting for half of the
province's foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
From 1978 to 1996, trade value between Fujian and Hong Kong was
38 billion US dollars, accounting for half the province's foreign
trade volume.
</P>
<P>
In that time, Fujian imported 15 billion US dollars of goods
from Hong Kong, or 52.8 percent of its imports. It exported 22
billion US dollars of goods to Hong Kong -- 44.2 percent of its
exports.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Fujian had approved 12,600 projects
funded by Hong Kong investors. The contracted value was 27.1
billion US dollars, 60 percent of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has been the spring-board for Taiwan business people
who look for investment opportunities in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
About half the tourists visiting the province each year are
from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The steady growth of bilateral trade has supported Hong Kong's
foreign trade and shipping industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
