<HEADLINE> Scalfaro Says Secession Unconstitutional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro
said today that Italy is indivisible and secession is
constitutionally banned.
</P>
<P>
His remarks are made in response to the secession calls of the
separatist Northern League party and its outspoken leader Umberto
Bossi.
</P>
<P>
"Secession is, according to our constitution, a
constitutionally illegal act," the president said.
</P>
<P>
He said the 1948 Constitution states that Italy is one and
indivisible.
</P>
<P>
The president said he agreed to talks of autonomy and
federalism, but not secession.
</P>
<P>
The Northern League switched to separatism from federalism last
year after it failed to win the balance of power in parliamentary
elections.
</P>
<P>
Last year, it even held a symbolic declaration of independence
for "Padania", a name Bossi has given to his nebulous state which
has no recognized powers, institutions or borders. 
