<HEADLINE> Mineral Discoveries in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese geologists have discovered 32
kinds of minerals that have industrial potential in Tibet, of
which chromite, copper, boron, and 13 others are among the
country's top 10 in terms of reserves.
</P>
<P>
Tibet is rich in mineral resources, with proven copper reserves
of 8.7 million tons and has the country's largest porphyry copper
belt.
</P>
<P>
Geologists have also found large chromite reserves in the
southern part of the region. Proven chromite reserves there amount
to five million tons.
</P>
<P>
Proven boron reserves amount to over 30 million tons and large
placer gold deposits and several other mid-sized deposits have
also been found.  
</P>
</TEXT>
