<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. To Lift Embargo to Ecuadoran Shrimp Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The United States decided to lift the
embargo to the imports of shrimp from Ecuador, the U.S. embassy
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Department of State determined that Ecuador is really
trying to guarantee the life of marine turtles in danger of
extinction during the capture of shrimp, said the embassy in a
communique.
</P>
<P>
The decision of the Department of State was based on the recent
inspections made to Ecuadoran shrimping boats.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadoran authorities said Wednesday they were confident
the U.S. shrimp embargo would be lifted from June 1.
</P>
<P>
The United States imposed the embargo May 1 considering that
the Ecuadoran shrimping boats did not used adequately the devices
to release the turtles during the capture of shrimp.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. embassy said that the U.S. government had
congratulated the Ecuadoran Foreign Trade Ministry for having
shrimpers use the devices that protect the turtles.
</P>
<P>
The shrimp embargo caused Ecuadoran shrimpers losses of up to
5 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
