<HEADLINE> Gotti Takes Stage and Overall Lead in Tour of Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian cyclist Ivan Gotti won the
14th stage of the Tour of Italy on Saturday and took the overall
leaders pink jersey off Pavel Tonkov of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Gotti, fifth in the 1995 Tour de France and
fifth in this race last year, came home alone with Tonkov trailing
in one minute and 46 seconds behind while Frenchman Luc Leblanc,
second overall overnight, was more than three minutes behind.
</P>
<P>
Gotti, who beat compatriot Nicola Miceli into second place on
the stage, leads Tonkov, last year's winner, by 51 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Tonkov's compatriot Piotr Ugromov, 12th overnight, failed to
start the stage and was taken to hospital suffering from a fever,
doctors said that he would be kept in for the next two days.
</P>
