<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Crude Oil Basket Price Drops 45 cents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The basket price of crude oils and
byproducts of Venezuela at the close of the week indicates a 45
cent drop compared to that of last week, according to data from
the Energy and Mines Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The reduction in the price was due to a growing offer of crudes
and byproducts in the internatinal market, especially from the
members of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries
(OPEC), which increased production by 400,000 barrels a day,
in comparison to the month of march.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC basket price was quoted at 19.01 dollars per barrel at
the close of the week, while on Thursday and Wednesday it was 18.72
and 18.83 dollars per barrel, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
