<HEADLINE> Pankratov Fails in World Record Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Double Olympic champion Denis
Pankratov fell well short of his world record pretentions in the
men's 200 meters butterfly at the Canet international meeting on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian announced before the meeting -- his last before the
European championships in Seville in August -- that he was gunning
for his own world record of one minute 55.22 seconds, but he only
managed 1:57.34.
</P>
<P>
Pankratov was inside world record time in the first three
lengths but lost pace over the last 50 meters, a second
disappointment this week after his sixth place in Barcelona in the
100 butterfly.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica's Olympic champion Claudia Poll, in her first
long-course competition of the season, won the women's 200 meters
freestyle in a respectable time of 1:58.18 after only four weeks'
training in a 50-meter pool. 
</P>
