<HEADLINE> Brief Latin American Cultural News (2) Venezuelan Film Festival Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS -- The Venezuelan Film Festival ended Wednesday after a
week in which 28 full length features, 56 short length films, 15
documental films and seven cartoon films were screened.

Isla de la Libertad, an Uruguayan Historical Monument
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Uruguayan government declared national
historical monument the La Libertad island, located inside
Montevideo Bay, to preserve its colonial architecture structures
of military characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The site was the scenario of historical events of
transcendence in the history of Uruguay in the 18th and 19th
centuries.

Social Researchers World Congress Being Held in Colombia
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- The Social Researchers World Congress will
last from today until June 5 in the Colombian city of Cartagena de
Indias.
</P>
<P>
The forum will be attended by 500 experts in social sciences
from 61 countries, including Uruguayan writer Eduardo Galeano.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is sponsored by the United Nations Education,
Science, and Culture Organization (UNESCO) and several Colombian
organizations.

Deceased Writers To Be Remembered in Costa Rica
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- Late writers Isaac Felipe Azofeifa and Fabian
Dobles will be paid homage this weekend by the Costa Rican Culture
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Azofeifa and Dobles were famous not only for their literary
work, but also for their political militancy and their concern for
the social situation of their country, together with novel writer
Joaquin Gutierrez.
</P>
<P>
Poet Azofeifa and narrator Dobles belong to the so-called
"Generation of the Forties" and died recently. enditem


nnnn
