<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets Greek Prefecture Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Crete(Greece), May 31 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese leader Li
Ruihuan met with Crete Prefecture Governor Stavros Kambelis of
Greece here today, both expressing the hope that Sino-Greek
friendship and cooperation will grow further.
</P>
<P>
After extending warm welcome to li, Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, Kambelis stressed the importance of Crete in the
Greek, European and world culture, saying that there is similarity
between the Greek and Chinese culture.
</P>
<P>
He said that Crete enjoys special natural advantage in
developing the economy, and its tourism, agriculture and science
and technology have their own characteristics.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he added, personal exchanges between his
prefecture and China in the relevant industries have increased. He
said that he hopes such exchanges will promote mutually beneficial
cooperation between Greece and China.
</P>
<P>
Li spoke highly of the important status of Crete in the history
of the Greek civilization. He said that the Chinese people greatly
admire the Crete people's efforts to build their hometown into an
area with well-developed tourism, agriculture, science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China attaches importance to Sino-Greek
governmental exchanges and contacts.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hopes his current visit will help exchange
mutual understanding between the Chinese and Greek Peoples.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
